<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName LSID="238C7919-F7AC-5E92-B3A1-9A4F53C0EC0A" authority="(Gervais, 1842)" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1842" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eubalta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eubalta planiceps" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planiceps">Eubalta planiceps (Gervais, 1842)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Sadocus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sadocus planiceps" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planiceps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Sadocus planiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(originally 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin" authorityYear="1838" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Gonyleptes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gonyleptes planiceps" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planiceps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Gonyleptes planiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gervais, 1842) has a convoluted taxonomic history, with many previously unknown synonyms detected, which will be published elsewhere (briefly commented in 
<bibRefCitation author="Pessoa-Silva, M" editor="Kury, AB" journalOrPublisher="Version 1.0 - Checklist of all valid nomina in Opiliones with authors and dates of publication up to 2018. Self published, Rio de Janeiro" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="58 - 59" refId="B65" refString="Pessoa-Silva, M, Hara, M, Pinto-da-Rocha, R, 2020. Chapter 12. Pachylinae at their southernmost extreme (Laniatores: Gonyleptidae). In: Kury, AB, Mendes, AC, Cardoso, L, Kury, MS, Granado, AA, Eds., WCO-Lite: online world catalogue of harvestmen (Arachnida, Opiliones). Version 1.0 - Checklist of all valid nomina in Opiliones with authors and dates of publication up to 2018. Self published, Rio de Janeiro: 58 - 59" title="Chapter 12. Pachylinae at their southernmost extreme (Laniatores: Gonyleptidae)." volumeTitle="WCO-Lite: online world catalogue of harvestmen (Arachnida, Opiliones)." year="2020">Pessoa-Silva et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). We excluded it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sorensen" authorityYear="1886" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Sadocus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sadocus" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Sadocus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it lacks the synapomorphies of the genus. It also lacks the diagnostic characters of the genus, such as the typical ocularium shape and type of armature, dorsal scutum shape, just to name a few. Comparing with other species of Chilean 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sorensen" authorityYear="1884" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pachylinae">Pachylinae</taxonomicName>
, we detected striking similarities with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eubalta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eubalta meridionalis" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Eubalta meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This synonymy did not go unnoticed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kury, AB" journalOrPublisher="Self published, Rio de Janeiro" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B40" refString="Kury, AB, Mendes, AC, Cardoso, L, Kury, MS, Granado Ade, A, 2020a. WCO-Lite: online world catalogue of harvestmen (Arachnida, Opiliones). Version 1.0 - Checklist of all valid nomina in Opiliones with authors and dates of publications up to 2018. Self published, Rio de Janeiro" title="WCO-Lite: online world catalogue of harvestmen (Arachnida, Opiliones). Version 1.0 - Checklist of all valid nomina in Opiliones with authors and dates of publications up to 2018." year="2020 a">Kury et al. (2020a)</bibRefCitation>
in his catalogue, who also detected this in parallel with this revision. Finally, Kury et al. kindly invited us to publish this synonymy that resulted in a publication of that synonymy (
<bibRefCitation author="Pessoa-Silva, M" editor="Kury, AB" journalOrPublisher="Version 1.0 - Checklist of all valid nomina in Opiliones with authors and dates of publication up to 2018. Self published, Rio de Janeiro" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="58 - 59" refId="B65" refString="Pessoa-Silva, M, Hara, M, Pinto-da-Rocha, R, 2020. Chapter 12. Pachylinae at their southernmost extreme (Laniatores: Gonyleptidae). In: Kury, AB, Mendes, AC, Cardoso, L, Kury, MS, Granado, AA, Eds., WCO-Lite: online world catalogue of harvestmen (Arachnida, Opiliones). Version 1.0 - Checklist of all valid nomina in Opiliones with authors and dates of publication up to 2018. Self published, Rio de Janeiro: 58 - 59" title="Chapter 12. Pachylinae at their southernmost extreme (Laniatores: Gonyleptidae)." volumeTitle="WCO-Lite: online world catalogue of harvestmen (Arachnida, Opiliones)." year="2020">Pessoa-Silva et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
